response:
 This is a rational expression, the unknown (the diagonal in the matrix) of the Fibonacci sequence is given, can use Pell equation.
Let $x$ be a root of following equation
$$
\begin{aligned}
x-(1+x)=-\frac{x}{1-1}
\end{aligned}
$$
$$
\begin{aligned}
x=1-\dfrac{1}{x}\\
x^2-x+1=0
\end{aligned}
$$
$$
\begin{aligned}
x=\dfrac 1 2 (1+\sqrt{3})\\
x=\dfrac 1 2 (1-\sqrt{3})\\
x=\dfrac 1 2 (\dfrac 1 2 -\sqrt{3})
\end{aligned}
$$
So there is only positive reals, and the answer is $\boxed{x=\dfrac{1}{2} (\dfrac{1}{2}+\sqrt{3})}$
</think> <answer> $$\boxed{x=\dfrac{1}{2} (\dfrac{1}{2}+\sqrt{3})}$$ </answer>

